===Etymology===
{{dercat|zh|ine-toc-pro|cau-nec-pro}}
Possibly from {{der|och|txb|mit}}, from {{der|och|ine-pro|*médʰu|t=honey}}. Cognate with {{cog|en|mead}}, {{cog|nl|mede||mead}} {{cog|de|Met||mead}}, {{cog|sv|mjöd||mead}}, {{cog|sa|मधु||honey}}, {{cog|grc|μέθυ||wine}}, {{cog|cu|медъ||honey}}, {{cog|ru|мёд||honey}}, {{cog|pl|miód||honey}}.<ref>{{cite-book|1=en|year=1998|author={{w|Alexander Lubotsky}}|title=The Bronze Age and Early Iron Age peoples of Eastern Central Asia|chapter=Tocharian Loan Words in Old Chinese: Chariots, Chariot Gear, and Town Building|chapterurl=https://scholarlypublications.universiteitleiden.nl/access/item%3A2883003/view|pages=379-390}}</ref>

Sense “mistress, young girl” is additionally a {{psm|zh|en|miss|nocap=1}}.

